  "text": "The unified alerting pipeline flows as follows: (1) **Scheduler** (`schedule.go`): `schedule.Run()` starts a ticker loop via `schedulePeriodic()`, which on each tick calls `processTick()` to fetch schedulable rules, determine which are ready to evaluate, and send evaluations to per-rule goroutines. (2) **Rule evaluation** (`alert_rule.go` + `eval.go`): Each `alertRule.Run()` goroutine listens on `evalCh` for evaluation signals. On receiving one, `alertRule.evaluate()` creates a `ConditionEvaluator` via the `EvaluatorFactory`, calls `Evaluate()` which executes the SSE expression pipeline and converts results to `eval.Results` (Normal/Alerting/Pending/NoData/Error). (3) **State transitions** (`state/manager.go` + `state/state.go`): `stateManager.ProcessEvalResults()` processes each eval result, calling `state.transition()` which applies the state machine logic (`resultNormal`, `resultAlerting`, `resultNoData`, `resultError`) handling For duration, KeepFiringFor, and resolved detection. (4) **Notification dispatch** (`alert_rule.go` \u2192 `state/compat.go` \u2192 `sender/router.go` \u2192 `notifier/alertmanager.go`): The `send` callback in `alertRule.evaluate()` converts `StateTransitions` to `PostableAlerts` via `StateToPostableAlert()`, then calls `AlertsRouter.Send()` which routes alerts to the internal `MultiOrgAlertmanager` (calling `alertmanager.PutAlerts()` which delegates to `GrafanaAlertmanager.PutAlerts()`) and/or external alertmanagers.",
